      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage hikes are a double-edged sword. On one hand, they can boost consumer spending power, which might benefit your cafe as people have more money to spend on coffee and pastries. On the other hand, they can also increase your operational costs, potentially squeezing your profit margins. It's a balancing act, but ultimately, if you're in a low-cost living area, the increased wages could actually attract more workers and customers, offsetting some of the higher costs.",
