      "content": "Data shows that while minimum wage hikes can strain small businesses, they don't always lead to closures. In fact, many small businesses adapt by increasing prices, improving efficiency, or even expanding their customer base. The key is to stay nimble and innovative. For your cafe, this could mean focusing on unique offerings, excellent customer service, and community engagement to differentiate yourself from larger chains. It's not a guaranteed win, but with the right strategy, you can thrive even with higher wages.",
